Key Match Events: The Jazz got key contributions from their second unit, including 36 points off the bench.
The Suns' efficient offense, particularly from Kevin Durant and Devin Booker, was a turning point.
The Jazz made a 9-4 run in the fourth quarter to get within three points but couldn't overcome the deficit.
Post-Match Reflections: Jazz head coach Will Hardy acknowledged the team's effort and noted that they just missed key shots.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz were shorthanded without several rotation players, including Johnny Juzang.
Isaiah Collier continued his strong play with eight assists and only two turnovers.
